---
layout: _html
---
{%- render "partials/header"
  , collectionsAll: collections.all
  , page: page
  , env: env -%}
<div id="notesContainer">
  <div class="note" data-note-url="{{ page.url }}">
    <div id="notesHeader">
      <div id="notesListHeaderWrapper">
        <h1>{{ title }}</h1>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="notesList">
      {%- for card in collections[collectionKey] reversed -%}
        <div class="noteItem" id="{{ card.data.page.fileSlug }}">
          <div class="noteWrapper">
            <div class="content markdown-body">
              <h2>
                <a href="{{ env.SERVER_ENV | append: card.url }}">{{ card.data.title }}</a>
              </h2>
              {{ card.data.description }}
            </div>
            <div class="metaInfo">
              <a
                class="noteURL"
                href="{{ env.SERVER_ENV | append: card.url }}"
                target="_blank">Permanent Link</a>
              Â·
              <time class="updatedAt">{{ card.date | postTime }}</time>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      {%- endfor -%}
    </div>
    <div class="noteFooter markdown-body">
      <p>Nowadays, I spend most of my time building softwares, which has become my default way of online expression. Currently, I'm working on
        <a href="http://slippod.com/">Slippod, a privacy-first desktop note-taking app</a>
        and
        <a href="http://textpixie.com/">TextPixie, a tool to transform text including translation and extraction</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>